The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Oct. 4: The flood toll rose to 112 today, though the situ-ation improved in the districts. Reviewing the state with the district magistrates through a videoconference, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said: Water levels of all rivers in the districts have receded. 

 Calcutta: The Employees State Insurance Corporation has raised the wage limit for those to be brought under ESI scheme from Rs 7,500 a month to 10,000. Employees who earn Rs 10,000 a month will get the benefits from October 2006. 

 Howrah: Two per- sons were killed and two injured when lightning struck a Kali temple in Howrahs Bagnan on Wednesday. They were playing cards inside.




